=== Arguments For Deconditioning

ME/CFS patients do show objective markers consistent with deconditioning: reduced VO#sub[2]peak, lower peak heart rate, and decreased muscle mass in some studies. Prolonged bed rest produces symptoms (orthostatic intolerance, fatigue, cognitive slowing) that overlap with ME/CFS. These parallels led clinicians to assume that reversing inactivity would resolve symptoms.


